<TITLE> Khaleda, Saifur pay tax on undisclosed money </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, August 1 (bdnews24.com)  The National Board of Revenue received more than Tk 150 crore in tax on the last day of the earlier deadline for people to legalise undisclosed money, NBR officials said Wednesday. High-profile politicians, bureaucrats and businessmen rushed to meet the July 31 deadline, officials said. Former prime minister Khaleda Zia legalised Tk 1.33 crore Tuesday by paying Tk 33.37 lakh in tax, her lawyer Ahmed Azam Khan told bdnews24.com. The same day, former finance minister M Saifur Rahman "whitened" about Tk 1.3 crore by paying Tk 31 lakh in tax. NBR recorded the number of taxpayers under the amnesty at 3,511 until Monday but it shot up to 8,559 Tuesday. Total taxes collected by the NBR reached about Tk 300 crore Tuesdaythe last day of the two-month timeframewhich is a sharp rise from Tk 137 crore just a day before. The NBR Tuesday extended the deadline for legalising untaxed money by another two months to Sept 30, expecting a lot more prospective taxpayers. On June 5, the NBR set taxpayers the first deadline to legalise untaxed money through a two-month period ending on July 31. Under the amnesty, an additional 5 percent penalty was added to the normal tax rate. Khaleda, asked by the Anticorruption Commission to submit her wealth statement, legalised her "untaxed money" Tuesday, but is yet to submit her statement. bd
